         <div type="translation" xml:space="preserve"><head>Translation</head>
         <div type="translation" resp="#cmr" xml:lang="en"><p>Emperor Caesar M(arcus) Jul(ius) Philippus, Pious, Fortunate, Invincible [Aug(ustus)?], high priest [ . . .</p></div></div>
         <div type="commentary">
            <head>Commentary</head>
            <p>One of three milestones of Philip on this road: <ref type="inscription" n="M.195">M.195</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="M.197">M.197</ref>, <ref type="inscription" n="M.201">M.201</ref>, 
               with probably <ref type="inscription" n="M.160">M.160</ref>.</p>
            <p> For the remainder of the text cf. the milestone of Philip I at the tenth mile, <ref type="inscription" n="M.201">M.201</ref>.</p>
            <p>Line 3: The addition of the title Augustus lengthens the line surprisingly, as in <ref type="inscription" n="M.201">M.201</ref>, 
               but seems necessary.</p>
         </div>
         
